  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">National Initiatives for Sustainable &amp; Climate Smart oil Palm Smallholders Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2020, in Nigeria, 4,770 smallholder farmers were trained on Better Management Practices (BMP) and Sustainable Land Use (SLU) Practices in the 4 project states. There were 45 BMP plots and 209 Village Savings and Loans Associations (VSLAs) established, to enable farmer groups to build up their own resources and have access to inputs and markets. Stakeholder meetings were organized for the Nigeria NI-SCOPS Forum (NNF), State Ministry of Agriculture officials and CSOs. Additionally, the assessment and profiling of palm oil millers commenced, as well as the needs assessments for smallholder farmers&#x2019; skills and opportunities for livelihood diversification. Lastly, Memoranda of Understanding (MoU) were signed with two private sector investors.</narrative>
  </description>
